  Warwick R-user group is for everybody interested in R,
  the programming language for statistical computing, data
  science, visualisation and reproducible reporting.
  Warwick R User Group meets every 2 months to discuss
  R-related topics. At each session, speakers present
  interesting R packages (and how to make your own), share
  tips and tricks and offer advice to new R users.
  Everyone is welcome, regardless of R programming
  experience, from across or outside Warwick University. For
  further information, visit our Meetup.com page
  or contact a member of the WRUG
  committee.
  Warwick R User Group is supported by the R Consortium. We
  follow the R Consortium R
  Community code of conduct.













